  "time_ut": 1660736007,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc1\u0dba \u0d87\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf - \u0db6\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "My statement has been distorted by some media - Bandula",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mass Media Minister Bandula Gunawardena claims that some media have distorted the answer given by former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa to a question asked by a journalist whether he spends government money on his travels and other activities abroad.",
        "In the press conference held yesterday (16) at the government news department auditorium to announce the cabinet decisions of the week, a journalist mentioned that the fares of the private plane that former President Gotabhaya Rajapakse traveled from Singapore to the capital of Thailand were paid with the tax money of the people. The former president is still living under these privileges. asked a question.",
        "The minister states that in reply he stated that the former and current presidents are entitled to certain privileges by law. The minister pointed out that as the wife of the late President Ranasinghe Premadasa, Mrs. Hema Premadasa has been given those rights and privileges.",
        "\"Other than that, I did not mention anything about the former president or his trip from Singapore to Thailand. I stated that I can find out more details about it. Some media have reported today (17) that I said that the former president spent government money on his trip from Singapore to Bangkok. They have distorted what I said\", says Mr. Bandula Gunawardena.",
        "The question asked by a journalist at the press conference yesterday (16) and the answer given by the minister of mass media is as follows.",
        "Question - Minister, now our former president traveled from Singapore to Bangkok, Thailand. He used a private plane there. The money for this has been paid by the Government of Sri Lanka. This is the people's tax money. He still lives under these privileges, Minister.",
        "Answer - Yes. Because according to the Presidential Election Act of Sri Lanka, there are legal provisions on the privileges of the current and former president of the country. After the passing away of a former President, the lady also has a responsibility to provide such protection in my opinion. My general feeling is that Mrs. Hema Premadasa has been given those rights and privileges as the wife of the late President Ranasinghe Premadasa. I can go into more detail about that later."
      ],
